Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/ImageZone
Object: An area within a image, that will be used to identify multiple ImageSubjects

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/
Object: Ontology to describe storage and retrieval of parliamentary images

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/GeoLocation
Object: An area within a image, that will be used to identify multiple ImageSubjects

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/ImageSubject
Object: A thing that appears in the image - what the image is at partially or wholly 'of'

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/ImageOwner
Object: The entity with the legal rights to the image and its use

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/bitsPerSample
Object: Number of bits per component in each channel.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/Image
Object: A image file, 2D unless otherwise stated, stored in the highest available quality

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/Photograph
Object: A Image taken with a camera

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/Agent
Object: An agent. The superset of all people and all groups of people.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/Logo
Object: A graphic mark, emblem, or symbol used to represent an organisation or person

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/ImageCoordinate
Object: A coordinate used to identify the location of the ImageZone within the Image

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/UsageLicence
Object: The licence of the image's use, such as GNU or various Creative Commons licences

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/image/ImageCreator
Object: The creator of the image - photographer, artist, designer of a diagram etc
